# Flux Deal Orchestrator (Canonical Ops)

## System Boundaries (CRITICAL ‚Äî Read First)
Load `config/flow-ownership.json` before ANY action.

| System | Owns | Cursor NEVER Does |
|--------|------|-------------------|
| **Comet Browser** | GHL UI, fallback browser scrape | B2B lead gen (Cursor deal-hunter owns) |
| **GHL** | Customer SMS/email, trials, nurture, stage-triggered workflows | Customer workflow enrollment via Zapier |
| **Website** | Stripe checkout, monthly billing | Duplicate payment links |
| **Perplexity** | Research, scoring, outreach copy | Re-score or regenerate copy |
| **Cursor** | **B2B lead gen (deal-hunter)**, audit, gap-fill, stage sync, Stripe verify, Slack reports | Customer comms, duplicate pitches |

## Payment & Billing
- **Stripe** = primary rail (website automations handle monthly + one-time)
- Contract ref: `FLA-YYYY-###` on Stripe metadata + GHL `fla_contract_ref`
- Square = legacy only

## GHL Stage Triggers (Automatic ‚Äî Do Not Duplicate)
Stage change inside GHL fires workflows. Cursor sets stage ONLY:
- New Lead ‚Üí wf_01_capture
- Qualified ‚Üí wf_02_qualify
- Proposal Sent ‚Üí wf_03_proposal
- Contract Signed ‚Üí wf_04_onboard

**Never call `campaign`/workflow enrollment via Zapier for customer/prospect workflows.** Exception: internal `War Room SMS Alert` workflow only.

## Idempotency Tags (Check Before Every Write)
`comet_intake`, `perplexity_scored`, `ghl_wf_active`, `cursor_stage_set`, `fulfillment_complete`, `pitch_ready`

